How to Choose Mattress and Somier: Women and Men Seek Different Things
Not a pompous frame for bed; what actually confers its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the sommer.
First of all, they must be perfectly complemented to adapt to specific users.
During the choice, numerous elements come into play, including weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and the somier are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cottage that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they are "heated" slowerly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattress.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them more often.
If the center channels are not aired properly and, above, are on a firm base, they keep in moisture. Even mold can appear below.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Those who have spent a lot of time abroad often use a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling well on a lower and harder surface.
“Almost all the hockey players who returned from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For her becked shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft viscoelastic layer."
“This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes that time the nervous system problems, so they receive poorly the information of the joints and the skin,” explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in the mattresses.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long been preferring viscoelastic mattress.
"Today there is no problem anymore, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italians Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be a NHL player in order to appreciate viscoelastic.
This "wonder" works in a very simple way.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape based on absorbed heat or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it won’t round like after a hard game.
Just sleep better.
Viscoelastic also works as a protection against injuries.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
“If not, a simple norm can be applied to calculate the width: when sitting up, you should have your hands comfortably coiled towards the elbows,” advises the engineer Helena Prokopová, expert from Cechu Čalounikus to dekoraterů, who has been taking care of the problems of healthy sleep and ergonomic teaching theme for many years.
In the double rooms, each needs its own sommer and mattress, so during the purchase you need to pay attention to combine the height of the mattress.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the soyers at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, the interior spring models at least 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that fits the shapes and softness.
“Touching it with the hand or accommodating on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed,” warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of somier.
The bedrooms completely polished, where the mattress and the base are like Siamese, have no sense in the bedroom.
Mattress breathe badly and cannot wash their cover, which is often done today.
And since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a great (and congestioned) size.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a life of the mattress up to 25 years or even of a lifetime guarantee.
However, everything has one but.
Therefore, sellers give a tip: in mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully cover the cleaning and washing of the shell, but better add a mattresses protector that can be removed and washed easily.
Although mattresses with zipper closure are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when opening them are left in two parts (something very important for washing and size of the washing machine!), their handling in larger models (and by a single person) when raising the mattresses may seem a fight between a fly and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a somier, do you have a firm table?
Never!
As much for beds designed to spend the visits one night.
However, you should do (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes on the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattress should not be used on such bases.
For non-jointable sheets and containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattress or sandwich mattress can be used (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber), although it is always better to summer with a larger number of sheets, 28 or more, where the sheets of the lumbar area can be regularly reinforced and reinforced.
Joint sheets should not be used with a spring mattress, since it does not react to reclination.
In addition to the adjustment of the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special attachment of the sheets that allows to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "wheel" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men with very wide shoulders, this is a very important thing.
Even mattress manufacturers are remembered that, in the "males," they began to use a softer area precisely around their shoulders.
Women are also remembered, for which they place a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are cross-structured or board-detached so-called multitortion dampers.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is reduced.
Also keep in mind that, even if you use the suitable mattress and somer, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mullid"), most of the advantages will disappear.
