More parents use people tracking devices to control their children.
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for tracking vehicles, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old Anička Janatková.
At the moment the device has the approximate size of a crayon box, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a clock.
Many people were afraid of the missing Anička case and began to report on the available means to better protect their children.
Even the cost of invading your privacy.
“We all try to tell ourselves that it’s not about spying, but about another means to decrease the chances of a tragedy occurring,” says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the Czech market’s tracking device suppliers.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put into someone’s pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet topped ourselves with such cases.”
"Most customers really buy it for safety reasons," Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is used for and how it is used in an emergency case.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns that if the child doesn’t want to take him, he will simply throw him out.
"Even younger children show great creativity when they intentionally lose certain things if they want to avoid controlling them."
“Before, parents relyed enormously on mobiles, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” said Bočková.
In his opinion, it is discussible whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it’s a prepared kidnapping, the author will almost always check whether the child has any kind of electronic device that can reveal its location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is extended, it will also look for them, since their sale will certainly be done with much advertising."
“In such cases, criminals always go a step ahead of the police,” the psychologist says.
However, it adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack of a pedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the RC Monitoring company, who offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence may serve as a help.
“The device can be configured so that it regularly sends the position after a certain period.”
"If you suffer damage, it will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices carry an inclination meter integrated, so if the person simply slips down and remains immobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” said Čech.
In your opinion, such a service can be obtained even with smartphones with navigation, where special software should only be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment it is about devices with a size similar to a crate box or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they can be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, for that reason, tests are currently being conducted with devices that resemble a digital clock.
“Besides, they will have the added advantage that a possible aggressor may not identify the device.”
"Or identify it after a certain time, which can make the police gain time," he adds.
Although tracking devices are carried on the wrist or hanging, they will continue to use the same technology that is used for tracking vehicles.
